        <h3>Riverfront</h3>    
        <img src="https://ik.imagekit.io/dmrehbpdvz/download(1).jpg?updatedAt=1753283634509" alt="riverfront" align="right" height="250px" width="300px" style="border-radius: 30px; box-shadow: 5px 5px #AA7DCE;">
        <pre>
        <ul><li>The Sabarmati Riverfront is a waterfront development project in 
Ahmedabad, India,transforming the banks of the Sabarmati River into a 
recreational and public space</li>
            <li>The riverfront has boosted tourism, revitalized nearby 
neighborhoods, and spurred economic growth in Ahmedabad. It also hosts events
like the Ravivari Bazaar (Sunday market) and has become a popular venue for 
cultural events and festivals. 
            </li>
            <li>The riverfront features parks, gardens, promenades, event venues, ghats, 
markets, food zones, and children's play areas, providing a range of 
recreational opportunities. 
            </li></ul>
        <h3>Adalaj Stepwell</h3>
        <img src="https://ik.imagekit.io/dmrehbpdvz/download.jpg?updatedAt=1753284973724" alt="adalaj stepwell" align="left"  style="border-radius: 30px; box-shadow: 5px 5px #AA7DCE;" >
        <ul  style=" margin-left: 200px;"><li>The flamboyant 15th-century stepwell, has lost only little 
 its grandeur over the last few centuries.
        </li>
        <li>Till date, the intricate carvings on the pillars that support 
the five storeys are mostly intact; the beams work as pit stops 
for pigeons flying in and out and the structure still leaves jaws dropped 
for swarms of people.
        </li>   
    </ul>
     <h3>Sabarmati Ashram</h3>
     <img src="https://ik.imagekit.io/dmrehbpdvz/download.jpg?updatedAt=1753286683234" alt="Sabarmati Ashram" style="border-radius: 30px; box-shadow: 5px 5px #AA7DCE; " align="right" >
    <ul><li>Sabarmati Ashram in Gujarat, located north of Ahmedabad, was originally the
 residence of Mahatma Gandhi and his spouse Kasturba.
    </li>
    <li>The ashram is flanked by a calm and quiet stretch by the Sabarmati River.</li>
    <li>The original ashram was founded in May 1915 at Jivanlal Desai's 
Kochrab Bungalow, who was a barrister associate of Gandhi, as Satyagraha Ashram.
</ul>
    </li>
    <h3>Science City</h3>
    <img  src="https://ik.imagekit.io/dmrehbpdvz/download.jpg?updatedAt=1753286683234" alt="science city" align="left" style="border-radius: 30px; box-shadow: 5px 5px #AA7DCE; ">
    <ul style="margin-left: 300px;">
        <li>Gujarat Science City, located in Ahmedabad, is a sprawling 
complex dedicated to promoting scientific education and fostering
a culture of scientific inquiry</li>
<li>It offers a blend of education and entertainment through 
interactive exhibits, virtual reality experiences, and live demonstrations. 
The facility aims to make science accessible and engaging for all ages,
 with a particular focus on inspiring young minds. 
</li>
    </ul>
    </pre>
